{
  "updated_summary": "On the vibrant *Japan's Got Talent* stage, bathed in blue and pink neon lights and reflecting a star-shaped backdrop, Tetsuro, a man in a plaid shirt and brown pants, presented his black and white Border Collie, Sunny (also referred to as 'Yes'), who emerged from a 'THANK YOU' doghouse. Tetsuro, visibly emotional, knelt to embrace Sunny, whispering, \"Sunny, we'll always be together,\" a moment amplified by his earlier voiceover about painful understanding. Close-ups highlighted Sunny's expressive face and Tetsuro's tender actions as the audience applauded. The judging panel, including Hamada, Alice, Gackt, and Yamada, reacted with emotion and laughter. Yamada noted the challenges of animal acts not always following commands but praised Sunny's movement and cuteness, while Alice confirmed Sunny was the first animal act. Yamada expressed a desire to see more of Sunny's story in the finals, emphasizing the strong bond. Later, with the stage still brightly lit and the *Japan's Got Talent* logo prominent, Tetsuro confirmed his dog's name was 'Yes' (Iesu), eliciting applause. A judge in a black blazer and silver choker admired 'Yes's' performance, humorously calling its vocalization a \"dirty voice,\" which Tetsuro playfully corrected. Another judge, in a floral blouse, shared her puppy experience, finding the act cute and impressive, referencing a \"cunning\" comment. A final judge in a black vest and white shirt gestured enthusiastically, calling the dog cute and wanting to see more, amidst continuous audience applause and murmurs."
."
